+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01M66wAXgquTLNhyxLPHpMmK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me trace each bug:\n\n**Bug 1:** `EventBus` uses a module-level `globalHandlers` Map — handlers persist across test instances, causing cross-test contamination. When the inventory test creates a `new EventBus()`, it shares the same global handlers from previous tests, leading to duplicate/accumulated handlers that cause \"Insufficient stock\" errors because multiple handlers fire.\n\n**Bug 2:** `OrderRepository.update()` at line 38: `const updated = { ...updates, id, updatedAt: Date.now() } as Order` — this uses only `updates` and loses all existing fields. Should be `{ ...existing, ...updates, id, updatedAt: ... }`.\n\n**Bug 3:** `BillingService.registerHandlers()` line 25: `this.eventBus.on(ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED, this.handleRefund)` — missing `.bind(this)`, so `this.payments` is undefined when invoked.\n\n**Bug 4:** `InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled()` line 50: `if (eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled') return;` — the cancellation event doesn't have a `status` field (see `OrderCancelledEvent` type), so this always returns early and never releases stock.\n\n**Bug 5:** `calculateOrderTotal` line 23: `const total = afterDiscount + taxAmount;` — not rounded. Should be `Math.round((afterDiscount + taxAmount) * 100) / 100`.\n\n**Bug 6:** `refundOrder` line 99: `if (daysSinceCreation >= REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS)` — should be `> REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS` to allow refund on exactly day 30."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":439,"cache_read_input_tokens":38946,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":439},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e49fe5b8-dc0c-42fb-8743-c88d102fae00","uuid":"2f99b1f0-9704-45f1-8